post_text:
PCSS II will begin 1:1 Chromebook Program for All Students

Dear Families,

We have some great news to share. We at Pioneer believe that all students should have an equal opportunity to the same resources and quality education as their peers.

We will be providing Chromebooks to our all students.

All students will be issued a device to take to and from school.

Emails will be sent to parents with more details. Please contact us should you have any questions.

PCSS II Administration

Pioneer Charter School Of Science II added 36 new photos.
June 2 at 2:42 PM ¬∑

Mr. Alla and his APCSP students Misato, Kieron, and Shihab hosted a Zoom event for PCSS II on Saturday, May 30th to watch as a pirate family the launching of the Falcon 9 and Crew Dragon on their Demo-2 mission to the International Space Station, making history. After the launch, we hosted the Kahoot game with questions about astronomy and NASA. The next game students tried the ISS Docking simulator, which is the actual interface used by astronauts to train. PCSS II hopes to promote learning in STEM through events such as this in the future and witness important events together.
text:
Pioneer Charter School Of Science II added 36 new photos.
June 2 at 2:42 PM ¬∑

Mr. Alla and his APCSP students Misato, Kieron, and Shihab hosted a Zoom event for PCSS II on Saturday, May 30th to watch as a pirate family the launching of the Falcon 9 and Crew Dragon on their Demo-2 mission to the International Space Station, making history. After the launch, we hosted the Kahoot game with questions about astronomy and NASA. The next game students tried the ISS Docking simulator, which is the actual interface used by astronauts to train. PCSS II hopes to promote learning in STEM through events such as this in the future and witness important events together.

post_text:
We are deeply saddened and outraged by the killing of George Floyd at the hands of those who were sworn to protect. It was devastating to watch the video footage of the incident. We are in disbelief of how brutal actions like this can still take place in 2020. We grieve with his family and community.

Racism has no place in our society - today or in the future. We all stand united against bigotry, racism, and inequality.

Together we will battle injustice and make our world a better place for all.

Students competed remotely by submitting a video presentation of their Science Fair project titled Eco-Analyst: Interpretation of Environmental Conditions through Supervised Machine Learning.

Congratulations!

post_text: Charity Club will be hosting a Black History Celebration Event in the PCSS II Gym tomorrow, Friday, February 28. Black History Day will be celebrating the culture, diversity, and accomplishments of Africans and Afro-Caribbeans. There will be food, music, dance, and poetry. Dear Parents & Guardians;

Parent teacher conferences will be held on Thursday February 6th from 12:45pm until 5:45pm. Teachers will have a short break from 3:05pm until 4:05pm. There will be absolutely no parent meetings during this time. If you are planning on attending the parent teacher conferences, please use the SignUPGenius link provided in this email to choose a time slot to meet with teachers. Be sure to select a different time slot for which to meet with each teacher to avoid double booking the same time slot.

You will be able to change departments and choose different teachers by selecting the ‚ÄúShow More Sign Ups‚Äù tab in the upper right of the screen.

If you are unable to attend, we encourage you to contact your child‚Äôs teacher to schedule another time to meet with them.

As always, please contact the main office with any questions or concerns.

post_text:
We are saddened to hear of the passing of Peabody Superintendent Cara Murtagh.

We are here to offer our unwavering support for whatever is needed during this trying time.
shared_text:
Ted Bettencourt
November 29, 2019 at 6:21 PM ¬∑

I am very sorry to share with you the terrible news of the sudden and unexpected passing of School Superintendent Cara Murtagh.

Superintendent Murtagh‚Äôs talent, energy and can-do spirit inspired all those whose lives she touched. Her selfless devotion to our students, faculty and staff, combined with her lifelong passion for education, lifted the entire Peabody school community.

I was honored to work with Cara every day and proud to call her my friend. On behalf of our entire community, I have extended to Cara‚Äôs family our heartfelt sympathy and loving support.

Dear Parents and Guardians,

As you know, we have been asking for support letters for our Elementary School bid! With the deadline rapidly approaching, we are still looking for letters.

Below is a sample letter we have attached for your convenience. Please feel free to use that as a guide for your letter. You do not have to follow it if you wish to write one from scratch.

The deadline for these letters is this FRIDAY, October 11th. Please email all letters to Patrick - pshankhour@pioneercss.org.

You can also stop by his office at the school (located in Room 103) if you need extra help writing a letter.

Please reach out to us if you have any questions at all.

Thank you for your continued support!

post_text:
Flag Football Begins!

This past Wednesday the PCSSII Pirates headed to Everett to take on the PCSS Panthers in both schools first-ever varsity flag football game. The teams played two highly contested games in an afternoon doubleheader, which saw the Pirates fall slightly short in both games.

The team heads to Boston Prep for a doubleheader this Saturday and will play their first home game at Waybright Elementary School on Monday, Sept. 30. Kickoff at 5:00 PM.

post_text:
Dear Parents,

This is an important announcement from Pioneer Charter School of Science 2. This year, we are applying to open an elementary school! Part of this application process calls for support letters from our parents, family members, and community leaders.

This is where we need your help. Writing a support letter is as easy as telling the story of how PCSS has helped your student. I have created a sample template you may use to help. If you would like the template, please email Patrick, our Outreach Coordinator at pshankhour@pioneercss.org

The sooner we receive these letters the better! You can email me your letter, stop by my office to write a letter together, or bring a printed copy into the main office.

Thank you for your continued support in PCSS II!

Hello Parents,

Now the school is back in session, we wanted to send out a few friendly reminders!

- Students should not be picked up near our neighbors properties. Students should be picked up at the top of the hill.
- Parents should not he parking/using nearby driveways as a way of turning around.
- Students should never be on our neighbors properties (driveways, porches etc.)
- Main St should not be used as a pickup/drop off area.

Please help us in making our community as great as it has always been!

Thank you

post_text:
Dear Parents,

As many of you are aware, we are in the process of applying for a PCSS II Elementary School! Part of the application process calls for support letters from our parents. Letters from our wonderful parents would show the board just how well-received an elementary school would be for our community. If you would like to write a support letter, please reach out to our Outreach Coordinator Patrick Shankhour at pshankhour@pioneercss.org. He can provide answers to your questions, as well as some samples of what to say in the letter.

As always we appreciate your continued support in PCSS II!

PCSS II Administration
